<p>For each epidemic, the age‐specific burden of illness was assessed with the relative illness ratio (RIR).
 <xref rid="irv12620-bib-0021" ref-type="ref">21</xref> This ratio is defined as the contribution of the age group 
 <italic>i</italic> to ILI cases divide by its contribution to the general population: 
 <disp-formula id="irv12620-disp-0001">
  <math id="nlm-math-1">
   <mrow>
    <mtext>RIR</mtext>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mfrac>
     <mrow>
      <msub>
       <mi>C</mi>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </msub>
      <mo stretchy="false">/</mo>
      <msub>
       <mo>∑</mo>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </msub>
      <msub>
       <mi>C</mi>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <msub>
       <mi>N</mi>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </msub>
      <mo stretchy="false">/</mo>
      <msub>
       <mo>∑</mo>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </msub>
      <msub>
       <mi>N</mi>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </msub>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <italic>C</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub> is the number of ILI cases in age group 
 <italic>i</italic> and 
 <italic>N</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub> the total population of age group 
 <italic>i</italic>.
</p>
